This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it focuses on designing a new localizing system based on WiFi devices without any network infrastructure. It also involves signal processing techniques to resolve the ambiguity issue. 

It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the estimation of AOA (Angle of Arrival) which is a key concept in information theory. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the design of a dynamic and collaborative system for self-localization. 

cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is also a possible sub-category as the system is designed to be constructed with user's devices as network nodes, which can be seen as a multi-agent system. 

Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper may involve machine learning techniques for signal processing and localization.
